It was an Anomaly - with difficult start but also with many amazing moments in my life.
I started something absolutely new to me by creating my first Instagram AR filters. 
Thanks to the @sparkarcreators and @Instagram I had the honor to be one of the first 50 AR creators in their platform. And this changed my life. I found a new way to express my creativity thanks to the AR filters.
For the last 12 months I designed 100 AR filters which generated more than 10 billion of impressions! 
My Instagram account has grown from 1500 to more than 800k friends from around the world! Yes, I prefer to use the word ‚Äúfriends‚Äù than ‚Äúfollowers‚Äù, because I feel all of you guys, as my friends! 
I would not have created all of these filters without your support and respect to my work. 
Thanks to you guys, I learned some new words like ‚ÄúHola‚Äù, ‚Äú–ó–¥—Ä–∞–≤—Å—Ç–≤—É–≤–∞–π—Ç–µ‚Äù, ‚ÄúCiao‚Äù, ‚ÄúOla‚Äù and many others because you are from almost every part of this crazy world! My filters were used by some of the most influential people on Instagram like Bella Hadid, Kendal Jenner, Emily Raitakovski, Khloe Kardashian, Camilla Cabello, Chantel Jeffries, Diplo and many others...
The ‚ÄúFreckles‚Äù filter was one of the most used Instagram filters for 2019.
At the July I showed to the world @design_by_angel_petkov and my concept for the future of technologies - The AR glasses - Frames.
I visited some amazing places like Llorret de Mar, Cadaques, Tossa de Mar, Pubol - the home of the genius Salvador Dali and his muse Gala, Figueres, Barcelona and also many places in the always warm Greece!
I had the chance to speak in front of many young people from my own town.
I was a mentor for two talented students.
I was honored as a laureate in Bulgarian Forbes‚Äôs 30 under 30 talents.
I worked with some of the biggest brands.
This is just a little part of my journey in 2019. And all that after the hardest year in my life - 2018. 
I would like to say again ‚ÄúThank you‚Äù to all of you friends, which I would rather call ‚ÄúAnomalies‚Äù, you are all the best! I Love all of you, Blago ‚ù§

My new AR filter is now online. I believe that today is too easy to hate someone or something because of the Internet. It's really easy to say just "I hate this" without any arguments. But we can all face against the Hate thanks to the Art. We live in times where one simple word can change someone's life and I believe we have to be very carefull when saying something negative. Everyone deserves to be loved, everyone deserves some respect, everyone deserves to feel important part of this crazy world. This is why I created this Image Tracking AR filter. I just decided to say "STOP" to all the hate! And If you walk around the streets, you'll see the Stop sign. Let's add something to the meaning of this sign. Let's make it like a cause. When you see a Stop sign, just open your Instagram Camera and load my "STOP!" filter. Then share this ARt message to the world. Together we can change the world we'are living on.

MixMe @mixmeband is an acoustic duo formed by Georgi Zaykov and Edit Unjian in February 2018. Both musicians sing and play the guitar as well. They are very drawn into making original songs but do covers of songs as well. The cover songs evolve in all kinds of genders such as rock, pop, jazz, hip - hop, contemporary, evergreen and more. The band always manages to make very popular songs sound diferrent and in a new, acoustic, soft sound.
